parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front axle suspension system can cause premature wear of the steer tires, excessive vibration, and loss of steering control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Excessive vibration in the front end suspension system
premature wear of the steer tires
excessive wear of suspension components (shocks
pins
and bushings)
loose torque arm bolts
and shearing of bolts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: U-bolt problems can cause the front axle suspension system to fail, leading to premature wear of the steer tires, excessive vibration, and loss of steering control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: U-bolt failure
excessive wear of the steer tires
and excessive vibration in the front end suspension system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An overweight steer axle can cause the front axle suspension system to fail, leading to premature wear of the steer tires, excessive vibration, and loss of steering control, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Overweight steer axle
excessive wear of the steer tires
and excessive vibration in the front end suspension system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the instrument cluster can cause inaccurate or erratic readings of vital vehicle information, such as speed, fuel level, and engine performance, which can lead to unsafe driving conditions and potential accidents.
symptoms: The dashboard gauges are acting erratically
the dashboard gauges are not functioning properly
the dashboard gauges are stuck or frozen
the dashboard gauges are displaying incorrect information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls
the transmission slips or jerks
the vehicle loses power
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wiring harness problems can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to issues with various vehicle systems, including safety features, and potentially causing accidents or fires.
symptoms: Electrical system malfunctions
lights or accessories not functioning
unusual noises or sparks from the wiring harness.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive vibrations in the driveline can cause components to fail, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Excessive vibrations at specific RPM ranges
vibrations felt through the body and driveline
driveline components failing or unscrewing
driveshaft dropping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of control while driving
noises coming from the front of the vehicle
and in some cases
the tie rod breaking
leading to an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension components can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of control while driving
noises coming from the front of the vehicle
and the vehicle hitting a bump on the road and suddenly losing control.
